column5: Scheme Number associated with the Rewards Program
column6:
Group  identifies type of transaction like instore txn, gas or restaurants purchase.
For example :-
for Costco Canada we have 2 groups, 
AAAAA - Base group for Instore purchase and others, 
CGSRT -  Gas and restaurants purchase
column7:
This fields explains the type of accumulation. Following are possible values:
QMPB:-TYPE-ANN     VALUE 'A'.  -- Anniversary 
QMPB:-TYPE-DAY     VALUE 'D'.  -- Daily
QMPB:-TYPE-CYC     VALUE 'G'.  -- Cycle day
QMPB:-TYPE-LTD      VALUE 'L'.   --- Life to date
QMPB:-TYPE-MTH     VALUE 'M'.  -- Monthly
column8:
It is relaed to the above field. For example,
If accural is monthly then end-date would be updated to month end date.
If accural is daily then end-date would be updated to today's date.
